# Secrets & site config (`.config`)

Live secrets and site-local operator inputs belong under **`<repo>/.config/`**, not in the git tree. The `.config` layout **mirrors** the project paths it configures.

## Mirror rule

```
Repo (code)                                      Site config (secrets / inputs)
─────────────────────────────────────────────    ─────────────────────────────────────────────
terraform/components/<domain>/<comp>/<slice>/  →  .config/terraform/components/<domain>/<comp>/<slice>.tfvars
applications/… / docker compose needs          →  .config/docker/*.env
SSH for providers / hosts                      →  .config/.ssh/
Remote state backend                           →  .config/terraform/minio.backend.hcl
```

Examples:

| Code | Site file |
|------|-----------|
| `terraform/components/swarm/grafana/app/` | `.config/terraform/components/swarm/grafana/app.tfvars` |
| `terraform/components/swarm/vault/config/` | `.config/terraform/components/swarm/vault/config.tfvars` |
| Compose / host tooling env | `.config/docker/site.env`, other `docker/*.env` |

When you add a new Terraform slice, add the matching `.config/.../<slice>.tfvars` path — same domains (`swarm/`, `cluster/`, `remote/`, `network/`) and same slice names (`app`, `config`, `database`).

## Hard requirements

- **Do not** commit secrets, tokens, passwords, private keys, live `*.tfvars`, or live `docker/*.env`.
- **Do not** put secrets in checked-in `.tf`, pipeline scripts, Jenkinsfiles, or app source.
- **Do not** invent a second secrets tree (Vault-in-repo, root `.env`, `secrets/`, scattered `*.tfvars` next to code). Use `.config`.
- **Do not** add checked-in `*.tfvars.example` unless the operator explicitly asks (see `AGENTS.md`). Live inputs stay in `.config`.
- Pipelines default `CONFIG_DIR` to `<repo>/.config` (override only via `.config/docker/site.env` when the tree lives elsewhere).

## Tags & discovery

Every live tfvars / backend / `docker/*.env` under `.config` starts with:

```
# homelab-config: <config-id>
```

`<config-id>` = path relative to `.config` without the file suffix (e.g. `terraform/components/swarm/grafana/app`). Pipelines resolve by this id.

## Git

`.gitignore` ignores `.config/*` except a few documented READMEs / `*.env.example` stubs. Never force-add live tfvars, env files, or keys.

## Anti-patterns

```
# ❌ BAD — secrets beside code or in-repo examples that hold real values
terraform/components/swarm/myapp/app/secrets.tfvars
terraform/components/swarm/myapp/app.tfvars.example   # with real creds or as the live source

# ✅ GOOD — mirrored site file under .config
.config/terraform/components/swarm/myapp/app.tfvars
```
